---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Aside from '../../../components/Aside.astro';
import {cacheSidebar} from '../../../data/cache-sidebar';
import {Code} from 'astro:components';
---

<DocsLayout title="Eviction Policies" sidebar={cacheSidebar}
            description="Four eviction behaviours: TTL by access, TTL by write, max entries, and max memory">

    <h1>Eviction Policies</h1>

    <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 !mt-2 !mb-8">
        Four eviction behaviours — use one, several, or all together.
    </p>

    <h2>Expire after access</h2>

    <p>Evicts entries that haven't been read or written within a time-to-live window. The timer resets on every
        access:</p>

    <Code code={`import io.peekandpoke.ultra.cache.fastCache
import kotlin.time.Duration.Companion.minutes
import kotlin.time.Duration.Companion.seconds

val cache = fastCache<String, String> {
    expireAfterAccess(5.minutes)
}

cache.put("session", "abc123")

// Reading resets the TTL
cache.get("session")  // resets the 5-minute timer

// After 5 minutes of no access, the entry is evicted`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <Aside>Eviction is processed in the background loop, not on the calling thread. An expired entry might survive
        briefly
        past its TTL until the next loop iteration (default: 50ms).
    </Aside>

    <h2>Expire after write</h2>

    <p>Evicts entries that haven't been <em>written</em> within a TTL window. Unlike <code>expireAfterAccess</code>,
        reading an entry does NOT reset the timer — only <code>put()</code> does:</p>

    <Code code={`val cache = fastCache<String, String> {
    expireAfterWrite(5.minutes)
}

cache.put("token", "abc123")

// Reading does NOT reset the TTL
cache.get("token")  // timer keeps ticking from the original put

// Only a new put resets the TTL
cache.put("token", "xyz789")  // timer resets now`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <p>Use <code>expireAfterWrite</code> when the data has a known staleness window regardless of how often
        it's read — API tokens, DNS lookups, config values fetched from a remote service, exchange rates.</p>

    <Aside>If you need stale data to be refreshed rather than evicted, see
        <a href="/ultra/cache/refresh">Background Refresh</a> — it serves the old value while reloading in the
        background.
    </Aside>

    <h2>Max entries</h2>

    <p>Caps the number of entries. When the limit is exceeded, the least-recently-accessed entries are evicted first
        (LRU):</p>

    <Code code={`val cache = fastCache<String, String> {
    maxEntries(100)
}

// After 100 entries, the oldest-accessed entry is evicted
// when a new one is added`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Max memory usage</h2>

    <p>Caps the total estimated memory usage. Uses an <code>ObjectSizeEstimator</code> to recursively measure object
        graphs. When the budget is exceeded, LRU eviction kicks in:</p>

    <Code code={`import io.peekandpoke.ultra.cache.ObjectSizeEstimator

val estimator = ObjectSizeEstimator()

val cache = fastCache<String, MyData> {
    maxMemoryUsage(
        maxMemorySize = 50 * 1024 * 1024,  // 50 MB
        estimator = estimator,
    )
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <p>The estimator walks the object graph recursively, accounting for:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Object headers (16 bytes on 64-bit HotSpot)</li>
        <li>Primitive fields (1–8 bytes each)</li>
        <li>String content (header + char array)</li>
        <li>Collections and maps (header + pointers + elements)</li>
        <li>Nested objects (recursive traversal with cycle detection)</li>
    </ul>

    <Aside>Memory estimation is exactly that — an estimate. It's close enough for cache budgeting but don't treat it as
        a precise memory profiler.
    </Aside>

    <h2>Combining behaviors</h2>

    <p>Stack multiple behaviors for fine-grained control. All active behaviors are checked during each eviction
        cycle:</p>

    <Code code={`val cache = fastCache<String, ExpensiveResult> {
    expireAfterAccess(10.minutes)     // remove stale entries
    maxEntries(5000)                   // hard cap on count
    maxMemoryUsage(                    // hard cap on memory
        maxMemorySize = 100 * 1024 * 1024,
        estimator = ObjectSizeEstimator(),
    )
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Custom loop delay</h2>

    <p>The background eviction loop runs every 50ms by default. Adjust it for your use case:</p>

    <Code code={`import kotlin.time.Duration.Companion.milliseconds
import kotlin.time.Duration.Companion.seconds

// Faster eviction checks (more CPU)
val responsive = fastCache<String, String>(loopDelay = 10.milliseconds) {
    expireAfterAccess(1.seconds)
}

// Slower checks (less CPU)
val relaxed = fastCache<String, String>(loopDelay = 1.seconds) {
    expireAfterAccess(5.minutes)
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Custom coroutine scope</h2>

    <p>By default the eviction loop runs in a global scope. Pass a custom scope if you need lifecycle control:</p>

    <Code code={`import kotlinx.coroutines.CoroutineScope
import kotlinx.coroutines.Dispatchers

val scope = CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.Default)

val cache = fastCache<String, String>(scope = scope) {
    expireAfterAccess(5.minutes)
}

// When the scope is cancelled, the eviction loop stops`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>All behaviours at a glance</h2>

    <div class="not-prose my-8">
        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
            <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Behaviour</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Trigger</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Strategy</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-gray-400">
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>expireAfterAccess</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">No read or write within TTL</td>
                <td class="py-2">Time-based, resets on read + write</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>expireAfterWrite</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">No write within TTL</td>
                <td class="py-2">Time-based, resets on write only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>maxEntries</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Entry count exceeds limit</td>
                <td class="py-2">LRU (least recently accessed)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>maxMemoryUsage</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Estimated memory exceeds budget</td>
                <td class="py-2">LRU (least recently accessed)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><a href="/ultra/cache/refresh" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300"><code>refreshAfterWrite</code></a>
                </td>
                <td class="py-2">Write age exceeds soft TTL</td>
                <td class="py-2">Async reload; optional hard TTL evicts</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><a href="/ultra/cache/observability" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300"><code>onEviction</code></a>
                </td>
                <td class="py-2">Another behaviour evicts an entry</td>
                <td class="py-2">Observer — fires callback</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="py-2"><a href="/ultra/cache/observability" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300"><code>statistics</code></a>
                </td>
                <td class="py-2">Every cache operation</td>
                <td class="py-2">Observer — counts hits, misses, puts, evictions</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <div class="not-prose mt-8 flex gap-4">
        <a href="/ultra/cache/refresh"
           class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-brand-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-brand-500 transition-colors">
            Background Refresh &rarr;
        </a>
    </div>

</DocsLayout>
